  history thumb|left|thumb|135px|françoise d'aubigné , marquise de maintenon maintenon is known for its picturesque château de maintenon , first home to the family d’angennes , marquis de maintenon , later home of madame de maintenon , morganatic second wife of king louis xiv.   another tourist attraction are the ruins of the aqueduct of maintenon , built by louis xiv to carry water from the eure river to the gardens of the palace of versailles .

romance & history : mme . de maintenon was governess to this king 's out - of-wedlock children before she became his mistress c. 1670

